article.headline: San Francisco 65, San Diego 55
article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Rashad Green tied his career high with 21 points to lead San Francisco to a 65-55 win over San Diego on Saturday night. San Francisco (8-10, 2-1 West Coast) made 47.6 percent from the field and 18 of 22 free throws in the second half. The Dons, who trailed 25-23 at the break, opened the second half with a 20-9 run to go ahead to stay. Perris Blackwell, who finished with 14 points and eight rebounds, had seven points in the run. Devin Ginty scored 14 points to lead San Diego (3-15, 0-4), which shot just 36.4 percent, including 3 of 20 from 3-point range. Chris Gabriel finished with eight points and 10 rebounds. San Diego, which has been tied or ahead at halftime in all four conference games, has lost all of them for the Toreros' first 0-4 West Coast record since 2004.
